./.title: Introduction
./.body:
ITRE Documentation
The Institute for Transportation Research and Education (ITRE) is an institutional center located at NC State University.
This book is a living repository for ITRE related documentation. Pages in this document are pulled from their respective directories, allowing for an up to date representation of current and past styles.

brand/.title: Brand
brand/.body:
Branding and Assets
To maintain a consistent institute brand, ITRE logos and templates should be used for all institute materials.
If there is no pre-created template or logo available which meets your needs, the following guidelines can be used to match the existing ITRE brand.
NC State University
As an institute within NC State University, any of the approved NCSU branding can be used in ITRE materials in place of the ITRE branding. The ITRE logo should still be included in the work when possible. More information on NCSU branding standards can be found on the NC State Branding Page
Colors
ITRE colors match the NC State Base colors, with the Wolf Pack Red as the main color and the Reynolds Red as an accent or hover color. Rather than use a solid black, a dark grey color is preferred.

Typography
The ITRE typeface for logos, business cards, and other printed materials is Futura, with Garamond as a body font for materials with large amounts of text. On the web, the NC State Typography standards should be used instead.

Typography on the Web
The above fonts are primarily for printed material. When designing ITRE materials for the web, follow the NC State Branding Guidelines. An NC State Brand Bootstrap can be downloaded to make those typefaces available.



Logo
The ITRE logo should be used on all official ITRE materials, both digital and print. Please follow best accessibility practices when using the logo, such as choosing a logo with sufficient contrast and including alt text when displaying the logo online. Further variations of this logo can be found on the ITRE public drive. If you do not have access to the public drive, please contact your network administrator.

themes/generic.html.title: Generic
themes/generic.html.body:
ITRE Generic Theme
The Institute for Transportation Research and Education (ITRE) is an institutional center located at NC State University. The Research Theme is a Wordpress theme for displaying project abstracts with associated author bios and relevant documents.
Theme Requirements



Plugin
Version
Website




ACF Pro
5.3.8
ACF


NC State Utility Bar
0.1
NC State University



Features

Basic theme to match brand standards with NCSU
Font Page template with two column and wide widget areas
Staff Page with image and links to resume
Flexible Page Builder template using ACF fields
WCAG 2 AA Accessibility standards
Optional Color Schemes with Wordpress customizer
Responsive and mobile ready

Sage
This theme was created using the Sage boilerplate from Roots.
Features

gulp build script that compiles both Sass and Less, checks for JavaScript errors, optimizes images, and concatenates and minifies files
BrowserSync for keeping multiple browsers and devices synchronized while testing, along with injecting updated CSS and JS into your browser while you're developing
Bower for front-end package management
asset-builder for the JSON file based asset pipeline
Bootstrap
Theme wrapper
ARIA roles and microformats
Posts use the hNews microformat
Multilingual ready and over 30 available community translations

Setup
Edit lib/setup.php to enable or disable theme features, setup navigation menus, post thumbnail sizes, post formats, and sidebars.
Documentation
Sage documentation is available at https://roots.io/sage/docs/.
Colors
Color schemes can be selected through the Wordpress Customizer interface. Custom color schemes can be defined, although the colors may appear slightly different due to accessibility formulas in the theme. Overriding these changes may cause the theme to no longer meet accessibility standards.

plugins/add-ons.html.title: Add-Ons
plugins/add-ons.html.body:
ITRE Widget
The Institute for Transportation Research and Education (ITRE) is an institutional center located at NC State University.
This plugin adds institute specific functions and styling for use with Wordpress.
Plugin Features

Recent News Widget and Shortcode
NCSU Styled Breadcrumbs
Advanced Search for Research Papers (Posts)
Shortcake UI Support / Styling

Upcoming Features

Callout Widget and Shortcode with Icon Support
Social Media Widget and Shortcode for Single and Multiple Tweets/Posts/etc.
Shortcode to add Author Bio Section for Posts (For Use With Research)

Plugin Code
Files in lib are compiled in functions.php while style.scss and admin.scss compile front facing and admin styles respectively.
